This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as Chinese word segmentation and POS tagging. It also uses recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in language modeling. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) as it proposes a new neural network architecture for supervised and partially supervised learning. 

Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) as it includes experiments on handwriting recognition. 

The sub-category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) is also a possibility as the paper proposes a new approach to modeling joint probability distributions. 

Finally, the sub-category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) may also be relevant as the paper uses recurrent neural networks as a key component of its architecture.
